    <div class="arch-detail">
      <h3>LLM-Generated Proxies</h3>
      <p>When Object A wants to talk to Object B with incompatible interfaces, the LLM generates a proxy object that translates between them:</p>
      <pre class="arch-proxy"><span class="arch-accent">Object A</span>  в”Җв”Җв–ә  <span class="arch-highlight">Proxy Object</span>  в”Җв”Җв–ә  <span class="arch-accent">Object B</span>
          в—„в”Җв”Җ  <span class="arch-dim">(LLM-generated)</span>  в—„в”Җв”Җ</pre>
      <p class="arch-note">The proxy is a real object with a manifest, using the same message protocol.</p>
    </div>
